Question: Should the government provide free college education to everyone the same way it provides high school education? Explain your answer.
Answer:
Providing college and high school in the same manner is not a good idea. It would be a terrible burden on the taxpayers because the cost of college is not the same as a high school education. When education is provided by the taxpayers, the experience can only be as good as the economic area the college would be in. athis is the reason that high school educations are not as highly regarded in low income areas. Public colleges do get some of their money from the government. But the amount from the government is decreasing and colleges have the opportunity to get money from other sources as well.